<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec_interference-applications" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Interference Applications</title>
   <activity>
    <title>Diffraction Practice</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            
        </p>
        <p>
            A red laser with <m>\lambda = 633 \mathrm{~nm}</m> shines through a single diffraction slit. The angular width of the bright spot in the middle of the screen is 10 degrees. 
        </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Determine the width of the slit.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Predict what will happen (qualitatively) when a green laser shines through the same slit: will the pattern get wider, narrower, or stay the same?
            </p>
        </statement>
    </task>
   </activity>
   <activity>
    <title>Diffraction Grating Practice</title>
    <p>
        
    </p>
    <p>
        A green laser (wavelength <m>550 \mathrm{~nm}</m>) of intensity <m>1.5 \mathrm{~\mu W/m^2}</m> passes through a diffraction grating that is <m>3 \mathrm{~cm}</m> wide and has <m>600 \mathrm{~lines/mm}</m>, forming an image on a screen <m>5 \mathrm{~cm}</m> away.
    </p>
    <p>
        Where on the screen does the first bright spot show up?
    </p>
   </activity>
</section>